Invincible
Invincible is Mark Grayson's superhero alias. He uses his powers to protect people and fight evil.<SEP>Invincible refers to a superhero and related media franchise.<SEP>Invincible is Mark Grayson's superhero persona, representing his powerful abilities and commitment to justice.

Mark Grayson
Mark Grayson is the protagonist of the Invincible comic book series and its related adaptations.<SEP>Mark Grayson is the protagonist of the Invincible comics and animated series. He's half-human, half-Viltrumite with superhuman abilities like strength, speed, and flight.<SEP>Mark Grayson, also known as Invincible, is the protagonist of the comic book series and animated TV show. He develops superpowers at age 17 and struggles with his father's true identity.<SEP>Mark Grayson, also known as Invincible, is a superhero with Viltrumite powers. He possesses superhuman strength, speed, durability, and flight, but has weaknesses such as vulnerability to certain frequencies affecting his ears and occasional loss of composure.<SEP>Mark Grayson, also known as Invincible, is the main protagonist in the comics and television series. He possesses superpowers and grapples with moral dilemmas.

Omni-Man
Omni-Man is Mark Grayson's father and a powerful Viltrumite, who betrays his son.<SEP>Omni-Man is Mark Grayson's father, initially portrayed as a heroic figure but later revealed to be an alien conqueror.

Empire Viltrumite
The Empire Viltrumite is a villainous organization that poses a threat to Earth in the Invincible universe.

Amazon Prime Video
Amazon Prime Video is a streaming service offering access to a library of movies, TV shows, and original content, including Invincible.<SEP>Amazon Prime Video is the streaming platform that airs the animated series 'Invincible'.<SEP>Amazon Prime Video is the streaming platform where the animated series 'Invincible' is available.

Steven Yeun
Steven Yeun is the actor who voices Mark Grayson in the 'Invincible' animated series.

Viltrumite
Viltrumite refers to a race of powerful extraterrestrial beings known for their strength and longevity. This category encompasses individuals like Vilgax and other characters with similar traits.<SEP>Viltrumites are a fictional race of super-powered beings known for their strength and resilience.<SEP>Viltrumites are an extraterrestrial race of superpowered beings known for their immense strength and aggressive nature.

Viltrumites
The Viltrumites are a race of powerful aliens with conquering ambitions. They possess superhuman abilities and are led by Omni-Man.

Atom Eve
Atom Eve is a superhero who forms a romantic relationship with Mark Grayson and has a daughter named Terra.

Terra
Terra is the daughter of Mark Grayson and Atom Eve.

Atom Eve (Samantha Eve Wilkins)
Atom Eve is Mark Grayson's romantic partner and eventual wife. She is a powerful hero with energy manipulation abilities.

Terra Grayson
Terra Grayson is the daughter of Mark Grayson and Atom Eve, inheriting Viltrumite powers and becoming the third Invincible.

Oliver Grayson (Kid Omni-Man, Young Omni-Man)
Oliver Grayson is Mark's half-brother, born from his father Nolan's relationship with a Thraxan named Andressa.

Markus Murphy (Marky, aka Kid Invincible)
Markus Murphy is Mark's son, conceived through rape by the Viltrumite Anissa.

Nolan Grayson (Omni-Man)
Nolan Grayson is Mark's father, a powerful Viltrumite who initially presents himself as a hero but harbors ulterior motives.

Cecil Stedman
Cecil Stedman leads the Global Defense Agency, tasked with overseeing and regulating superheroes. His relationship with Invincible is complex, marked by trust issues and differing ideologies.

Conquest
Conquest is an ancient Viltrumite warrior who poses a significant threat to Invincible and Earth.

Angstrom Levy
Angstrom Levy becomes Invincible's arch-nemesis, driven mad by his experiments and ultimately met with death at the hands of Robot.<SEP>Angstrom Levy is a character in the Invincible universe and appears to have died, causing an emotional reaction from Mark Grayson.

Robot
Robot is a powerful android who plays a pivotal role in several events within the story. He kills Cecil Stedman and eventually decapitates Angstrom Levy.

Viltrumite Empire
The Viltrumite Empire is a tyrannical, multiplanetary civilization led by Thragg, seeking conquest and domination.

Global Defense Agency (GDA)
The GDA is a government agency tasked with overseeing superheroes and managing threats to global security.

United States Government
The U.S. Government interacts with Invincible and the Global Defense Agency, often embroiled in conflicts related to extraterrestrial threats.

Elara
Elara is a young girl who discovers a mysterious book and uses it to awaken ancient creatures.

The Book
The Book is a magical, animated tome containing secrets and instructions for awakening ancient creatures.

The Village
The Village is a secluded place where Elara lives.

The Abandoned Library

The Forest
The Forest surrounds the village and is where Elara follows the book's instructions.

The Crystal Dragon
The Crystal Dragon is an ancient creature awakened by Elara who is willing to grant a wish.
